<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-184-060 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 532 948</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  April 1 1991 n414 p2(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Legal VARs forced to adapt: changing vertical market sees a risein consolidations. (Value-added resellers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Grace, Tim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The maturing of the legal market niche is causing VARs to alterthe manner in which they prospect and grow existing business.andO;Many are being forced to develop and acquire additional productsand support capabilities as a way of serving a more savvy customerbase.andP;  Law firms are becoming more and more tenacious in theirchannel demands.andP;  VARs have responded by expanding their supportservices, software functionality and presence.andP;  Industry officialssay that times are tough for legal VARs.andP;  The recession haspermanently altered the manner in which the legal industry works.andO;Software and services drive the market, now; not hardware.andP;  Theconsolidation among law firms is the main force driving the trendin the value-added channel.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Value-Added ResellersLegal ApplicationsDealers and AgentsComputer RetailingMarket Analysis.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   1990 law-firm system purchases. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>